tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE genetic_sequences (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  organism_name VARCHAR(255),
  sequence TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Researches (
    research_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    researcher_name VARCHAR(100),
    organism_id INT,
    research_date DATE,
    research_notes TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (organism_id) REFERENCES Organisms(organism_id)
);

CREATE TABLE gene (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    gene_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    sequence TEXT NOT NULL,
    organism_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (organism_id) REFERENCES organism(id)
);

CREATE TABLE research (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    researcher VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    research_topic VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    gene_id INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES gene(id)
);

CREATE TABLE Organisms (
    organism_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    organism_name VARCHAR(255),
    organism_type VARCHAR(50),
    genetic_sequence TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Researchers (
    researcher_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    researcher_name VARCHAR(255),
    field_of_study VARCHAR(50),
    contact_email VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE Experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    researcher_id INT,
    organism_id INT,
    experiment_date DATE,
    experiment_result TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Laboratories (
    lab_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    lab_name VARCHAR(255),
    location VARCHAR(100),
    lab_head VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE GeneSequences (
    gene_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    organism_id INT,
    gene_sequence TEXT,
    sequence_length INT
)
